# Todo List App - React Native Assignment

A Todo list mobile app built with React Native CLI and TypeScript for Modulus Seventeen assignment.

## What It Does

- User can register and login (Firebase Auth)
- Add tasks with title, description, and priority
- Mark tasks as done
- Delete tasks
- See all tasks in a list

## Tech Stack

- React Native CLI
- TypeScript
- Firebase Authentication
- React Navigation
- Context API for state management

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── components/      # Reusable components
├── context/         # Auth & Task contexts
├── models/          # TypeScript interfaces
├── navigation/      # Navigation setup
├── screens/         # All app screens
└── utils/           # Helper functions
```

## Setup & Run
```bash
npm install
npx react-native run-android
```

Make sure you have:
- Android Studio installed
- Android emulator running or device connected
- Firebase project set up with Email/Password auth enabled

## Features Implemented

✅ User authentication (register/login/logout)  
✅ Add tasks with priority levels  
✅ Mark tasks as completed  
✅ Delete tasks  
✅ Clean dark-themed UI  
✅ TypeScript for type safety  
✅ Context API for state management  

